.TH NCP 1 "April 2026" "ncp 0.2.0" "NetCat++ Manual"
.SH NAME
ncp \- NetCat++ networking toolkit with dashboard and system metrics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ncp
[SUBCOMMAND] [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
ncp combines scanning, transfer, text messaging, HTTP testing, sniffing, and a ratatui dashboard.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B ncp scan <host>
Scan a host for open ports.
.TP
.B ncp send <host> <port> <path>
Send file/directory payload.
.TP
.B ncp receive <port>
Receive file/directory payload.
.TP
.B ncp text-send <host> <port> <message>
Send plain text directly over TCP.
.TP
.B ncp text-listen <port>
Listen for plain text over TCP.
.TP
.B ncp http <url>
HTTP request inspector.
.TP
.B ncp sniff
Capture packets.
.TP
.B ncp dash
Open live dashboard.
.SH TEXT OPTIONS
.TP
.B --repeat <N>
Repeat sending message N times.
.TP
.B --interval <duration>
Interval between sends, e.g. 500ms, 1s.
.TP
.B --keep-alive
Keep text listener open for multiple messages.
.SH DASHBOARD
The dashboard includes packet traffic, throughput, top hosts, active connections, CPU/memory, top processes, and best-effort iGPU usage on macOS.
.SH PERMISSIONS
Packet capture typically requires elevated privileges:
.B sudo ncp sniff
or
.B sudo ncp dash
.SH ANDROID
Android builds provide system panels. Raw packet capture/sniffer paths are disabled in this build.
